# HobiHobby — Project Context

## Product Stage
Solo founder, early MVP. Live on Firebase Hosting at hobihobby.com.
Quality over speed. No hard launch deadline.

## Active Sprint: Sprint 4 — Local Discovery

### Sprint 4 Scope
- Hobby Map — Google Maps + Places API
- Nearby classes, workshops, stores, clubs — `findNearbyPlaces` Cloud Function (done)
- Hobby events feed
- Hobby compatibility matching — "find someone at your level nearby"
- Community Circles — groups by hobby + skill level + location

### Sprint 4 Rules
- Do NOT build mood-based recommendations yet → Sprint 5
- Do NOT build payments/monetization yet → Sprint 6
- UAE: start with Abu Dhabi only — nail local data quality before expanding to Dubai
- Gate Community Circles behind a minimum local user count — empty groups kill momentum
- All AI/API calls go through Firebase Cloud Functions — never expose API keys in frontend
- Cloud Functions use the **v2 SDK** (`firebase-functions/v2/https`)
- AI model: `gemini-2.5-flash` for quiz + coach, `gemini-2.5-flash-lite` for summarization
- Google Maps/Places key stored as a Cloud Functions secret (`GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY`)

## Architecture Decisions (Locked)
- **Firebase-native only.** No Express backend in production, no MongoDB, no Mongoose. Firestore is the single source of truth.
- **No micro-frontends.** Legacy `root-config/` and `micro-frontends/` scaffolding exists — ignore it. All active dev is in `web/`.
- **All AI calls through Cloud Functions.** Gemini API key lives only in Firebase Functions secrets.
- **Cloud Functions v2 SDK only.** Import from `firebase-functions/v2/https`, not the legacy v1 API.
- **Firebase Hosting only.** Vercel is decommissioned.

