## Coding Standards
- **TypeScript**: Strict mode, no `any`. Prefer `interface` for objects, `type` for unions.
- **React**: Functional components, typed props, custom hooks for reusable logic.
- **State**: Redux Toolkit for global, `useState` for local UI.
- **Styling**: TailwindCSS with `cn()` helper for conditional classes.
- **Cloud Functions**: v2 SDK, secrets via options, always check `request.auth`.
- **Git**: Conventional commits (`feat:`, `fix:`, `refactor:`, `docs:`, `chore:`).

## Common Gotchas
1. `signInWithPopup` breaks → use `signInWithRedirect` + `getRedirectResult`
2. `functions.runWith` not a function → that's v1; use v2 `onCall`
3. White screen locally → missing `VITE_FIREBASE_*` env vars; `isFirebaseConfigured` flag handles this
4. Backend crash on startup → placeholder Firebase private key; `initializeFirebase()` detects and skips it
5. Firestore rules `mismatched input '{'` → stray character at top; select all and repaste
6. Cloud Function 500 with `AxiosError 404` from `generativelanguage.googleapis.com` → the hardcoded Gemini model was retired (e.g. `gemini-2.0-flash` shut down June 1, 2026); check the [Gemini API changelog](https://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/docs/changelog) and update `GEMINI_MODEL` in `functions/index.js`
7. Cloud Function 500 "Failed to parse ... as JSON" → Gemini 2.5 models think by default and thinking tokens are drawn from `maxOutputTokens`, truncating the JSON before it closes; set `generationConfig.thinkingConfig.thinkingBudget: 0` to disable thinking for structured-output calls
8. `findNearbyPlaces` 500 or `REQUEST_DENIED` from Places API → `GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY` secret not set (`firebase functions:secrets:set GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY`) or the Places API isn't enabled for the project in Google Cloud Console
9. Google Sign-In redirect silently fails / bounces back to `/login` → two distinct causes, same symptom: (a) `hobihobby.com` is blocked by Etisalat (misclassified as "Pornography Web Sites", confirmed via `curl` — HTTPS resets, HTTP returns a `safe.etisalat.ae` page) as of Jul 2026; (b) **`VITE_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN` must match the exact origin the app is hosted on** — pointing it at a *different* Firebase domain than the hosting origin (e.g. `authDomain=...firebaseapp.com` while hosted at `...web.app`) breaks the redirect's cross-origin storage handshake in browsers with third-party storage partitioning (Safari ITP, Brave, Chrome partitioning, Firefox ETP). Fix: set `authDomain` to whichever domain is actually serving the app (currently `hobihobby-65e1a.web.app`). Submit a reclassification/appeal request to Etisalat before relying on `hobihobby.com` for anything user-facing again

## Decision Log
| Decision | Reasoning |
|---|---|
| Firebase-only backend | Solo founder; minimize ops overhead |
| Gemini Flash over Gemma 4 | Better structured JSON reliability; cost difference negligible at MVP |
| Migrated 2.0 Flash → 2.5 Flash (Jul 2026) | Gemini 2.0 Flash / Flash-Lite were shut down by Google on June 1, 2026 |
| No micro-frontends | Zero benefit for solo founder |
| Cloud Functions v2 | v1 deprecated and broke deployment |
| Art & Craft vertical first | Low barrier, tangible outputs, calming — matches target user |
| Google Places Text Search + Details (not Nearby Search) | Text Search lets us combine hobby name + intent (class/store/event) in one query string; Details call is limited to the nearest 10 results (post-distance-sort) to cap billed usage |

## Do NOT
- Suggest features outside Sprint 4 scope (no mood-based recs, no payments/monetization)
- Add MongoDB/Mongoose models
- Use `functions.runWith` (v1 API — deprecated)
- Put API keys in frontend code or `.env` files committed to git
- Add micro-frontend complexity
